 Researchers have discovered people who have breathing problems while asleep are more likely to experience an early decline in memory and other brain functions .
In a worrying study , they found that people with sleep apnoea - saw a mental decline more than a decade earlier , than those who had no sleep problems .
People who have no breathing problems are more than to experience early decline of memory to other sleep functions .
US researchers ' results suggested that the onset of Alzheimer 's might be accelerated among those with sleeping problems .